s are fetched","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"from the database. After that point, this property is always non-nil, but it","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"may be empty to indicate that no packs are present.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To detect when the shared offline storage object has finished loading its"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"packs"},{"type":"text","text":" property, observe KVO change notifications on the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"packs"},{"type":"text","text":" key path."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The initial load results in an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NSKeyValueChangeSetting"},{"type":"text","text":" change."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOfflineStorage\/packs","interfaceLanguage":"occ"},"references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOfflineStorage":{"fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNOfflineStorage"}],"role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"MLNOfflineStorage implements a singleton (shared object) that manages offline"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"packs and ambient caching. All of this class’s instance methods are asynchronous,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reflecting the fact that offline resources are stored in a database. The shared"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"object maintains a canonical collection of offline packs in its "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"packs"},{"type":"text","text":" property."}],"title":"MLNOfflineStorage","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOfflineStorage","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnofflinestorage"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS/ManageOfflineRegionsExample":{"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre-nat